  "instructions": [
    "Heat the sesame oil in a wok over medium heat.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger, stir until fragrant, about 30 seconds.",
    "Add the cooked fry-grind rice, break up clumps, and stir-fry for 2 minutes.",
    "Pour in the low-sodium soy sauce, honey, and rice vinegar, tossing to coat the rice evenly.",
    "Cook for another 2 minutes, allowing the glaze to thicken slightly.",
    "Fold in the chopped tarragon leaves and sprinkle with salt and black pepper.",
    "Continue to stir-fry for 1 minute until the rice is shiny and heated through.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with a few extra tarragon leaves if desired."
